==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Treasonable
<hw>Trea"son*a*ble</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>Pertaining to
treason; consisting of treason; involving the crime of treason, or
partaking of its guilt.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Most men's heads had been intoxicated with imaginations of plots
and <qex>treasonable</qex> practices.</q>
<rj><qau>Clarendon.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><syn><b>Syn.</b> -- Treacherous; traitorous; perfidious;
insidious.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p>--<wordforms><wf>Trea"son*a*ble*ness</wf>, <pos>n.</pos> --
<wf>Trea"son*a*bly</wf>, <pos>adv.</pos></wordforms>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Treasonous</ent>⟦br⟧
